#=GF CC   This family is involved in the cell-cycle surveillance mechanism
#=GF CC   called the spindle checkpoint. This mechanism monitors the
#=GF CC   proper bipolar attachment of sister chromatids to spindle
#=GF CC   microtubules and ensures the fidelity of chromosome segregation
#=GF CC   during mitosis. A key player in mitosis is Mad2, and Mad2
#=GF CC   exhibits an unusual two-state behaviour. A Mad1-Mad2 core
#=GF CC   complex recruits cytosolic Mad2 to kinetochores through Mad2
#=GF CC   dimerisation and converts Mad2 to a conformer amenable to Cdc20
#=GF CC   binding. p31comet inactivates the checkpoint by binding to Mad1-
#=GF CC   or Cdc20-bound Mad2 in such a way as to stop Mad2 activation and
#=GF CC   to promote the dissociation of the Mad2-Cdc20 complex [1].
